    <h3>Dosa Recipe </h3>
    <img src="https://www.awesomecuisine.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/Plain-Dosa.jpg" alt="">
    <p>
     Dosa is a traditional and ever popular South Indian breakfast
     dish made from a fermented rice and urad dal (black gram) batter,
     spread thin on a hot griddle, creating a golden, savory, crispy
     crepe typically served with Coconut Chutney and Sambar for a 
     flavorful and wholesome meal.
 </p>
    <h2>What Goes Into This Recipe 游대 With Helpful Swaps</h2>
